  <div class="mt-5">
    <h2 class="text-center" style="font-size:1.5rem;">Things to consider before <strong>Renting an Apartment</strong></h2>
  </div>


<section class="cd-faq">

	<ul class="cd-faq-categories">

		<li><a class="selected" href="#basics">Basics</a></li>

	</ul> <!-- cd-faq-categories -->

   <div class="cd-faq-items">
      <ul id="basics" class="cd-faq-group">
				<br>
				<br>
			 <br>
			 <br>
			 <br>

         <li>


            <a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">1. Payment method</a>
            <div class="cd-faq-content">
               <!-- content here -->
               The rent is usually paid in every 6 or 12 months in advance, or in some cases 3 months
                in advance. (The apartment price can be bargained for longer payment interval)
            </div>
         </li>

         <li>
            <a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">2. Apartment booking</a>
            <div class="cd-faq-content">
               <!-- content here -->
               Once you are satisfied with the apartment, the contract is signed on the same day. In a
               rare case like the contract couldn’t be signed after viewing, the apartment is booked. The
               booking fee ranges from 500 RMB to one months rent. It paid to the landlord as an
               insurance. Once the apartment is booked, the landlord can not give the apartment to
               someone else. In an unfortunate case, if the landlord gives the apartment to someone
               else then you will be compensated twice the deposited amount. And if lesser decides not
               to rent the apartment, the landlord will keep the deposit as a compensation.
            </div>
         </li>

         <li>
            <a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">3. Security deposit</a>
            <div class="cd-faq-content">
               <!-- content here -->
               Usually one month's rent is paid to the landlord as a security deposit when signing the
               contract. The security deposit will be returned to the lessee at the end of the contract
               after checking the apartment for damages. The damages to the apartment should be
               repaired before renting out or will be deducted from the security deposit.
            </div>
         </li>

         <li>
            <a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">4. Agency fee</a>
            <div class="cd-faq-content">
               <!-- content here -->
               The real estate agency fee is half of one month’s rent all over china, paid when signing
               the contract. However, we always provide our clients with discounts. The discount
               amount varies with various situations.
            </div>
         </li>

         <li>
            <a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">5. Repairs</a>
            <div class="cd-faq-content">
               <!-- content here -->
               All the equipment and appliances and the apartment is checked for their usual working
               condition before signing the contract. For the first month, all of the repairs is handled by
               the landlord. Starting from the second month the repairs are to be done by the lessee.
            </div>
         </li>

         <li>
            <a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">6. Police registration</a>
            <div class="cd-faq-content">
               <!-- content here -->
               According to the regulations of Nanjing government, all the foreigners who move to a
               new place should register in the local police station within 24 hours from the beginning
               of the contract. The fine for failing to do so is 2000 yuan maximum.
            </div>
         </li>

         <li>
            <a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">7. Utility bills payment</a>
            <div class="cd-faq-content">
               <!-- content here -->
               According to the regulations of Nanjing government, all the foreigners who move to a
               new place should register in the local police station within 24 hours from the beginning
               of the contract. The fine for failing to do so is 2000 yuan maximum.
            </div>
         </li>

         <li>
            <a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">8. Viewing charges</a>
            <div class="cd-faq-content">
               <!-- content here -->
               Our clients are picked up at their location and dropped off after viewing the apartments
               in our company car. The fee up to 50 RMB depending on the distance. The viewings are
               free for viewing was the nearby apartments.
            </div>
         </li>

         <li>
            <a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">9. After sales services</a>
            <div class="cd-faq-content">
               <!-- content here -->
               We help foreigners with house moving service at a lower price than the usual Chinese
               companies price. Other services include housecleaning, locksmith, cooking maid and so
               on. After signing the contract, our clients can contact us anytime whenever they have
               issues like repair needs, bills payment, police registration.
            </div>
         </li>

         <li>
            <a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">10. Things to carry with you to sign rental contract</a>
            <div class="cd-faq-content">
               <!-- content here -->
               Your passport, rent money or booking money.
            </div>
						<br>
         </li>
		</ul> <!-- cd-faq-group -->
	</div> <!-- cd-faq-items -->
	<a href="#0" class="cd-close-panel">Close</a>
</section> <!-- cd-faq -->
